  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a particle, two charged plates, and a magnetic field of strength B directed into the page. The two plates are parallel and horizontal with one above the other. The upper plate has a positive charge, and the lower plate has a negative charge. The particle is traveling with velocity v to the right parallel to the charged plates when it enters the magnetic field between the plates.\" src=\"/images/a076c9e0f64af6fee24193a6d5c213b0.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A particle with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"q\"><math alttext=\"q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>q</mi></math></span></span> and negligible mass is traveling to the right with velocity <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span> when it enters a region between two charged plates containing a magnetic field of strength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> directed into the page, as shown in the figure, and an electric field directed toward the bottom of the page (not shown). The magnitude of the electric field between the plates is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\"><math alttext=\"E\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>E</mi></math></span></span>. Which of the following is equal to the net force on the particle as the particle first enters the magnetic field? The positive direction is toward the top of the page.</p>\n",
